<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06344200 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06344200 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  CONSUMER; QA  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Q  I went to the Humane Society of Santa Clara Valley to adopt a dog. Youreceive numbers when you get there. Evidently the adoption supervisor calledmy number but I didn't hear it. They told me they called my number and nametwice. I had my hopes on a certain dog. I didn't get the dog. I talked to anumber of people there. I think the supervisor should speak up when callingnumbers. Please look into this.;   -- Al Hill, Sunnyvale  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Living  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  DOG LOVER ISN'T BARKING UP WRONG TREE  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Action Line  </MEMO><TEXT>  A  It took the Humane Society nearly two months to respond to this complaint.Cynthia Smith, Humane Society spokeswoman, apologizes to you for the problem.Smith says your name was called twice on a loudspeaker system. She had no ideawhy you didn't hear your name or number called. You are invited to return,because there's always a supply of dogs that need homes.;   Insuranceexplanation; Q  My son totaled his motorcycle on June 24 after owning it forjust one month. When he purchased the motorcycle, he bought an extendedwarranty for $295. I called the company that serviced the contract and wastold to return the contract and a refund would be processed. They weren't sureif the check would be sent to us or to Camden Honda, where my son bought themotorcycle. I've called Camden Honda but am not getting anywhere. If they gotthe money, they should send it to us.;   -- Dagmar Van Fleet, San Jose; A  Therefund is going to American Honda Finance Co., which financed your son'spurchase of the motorcycle, says Richard Birr, sales manager for Camden Honda.The insurance paid off the value of the motorcycle but didn't cover the fullamount of the loan, so American Honda finance has deducted the warranty refundfrom the loan balance.;   I.D. card will take awhile; Q  I received myresident alien identification card in early August. Unfortunately, it has mymaiden name on it. I wrote the Immigration and Naturalization Service on Aug.3 asking for a new card with my married name. I am getting concerned that Iwill not receive it.;   -- A.K., Redwood City; A  Not until next year, atleast, says an INS spokeswoman. She says it is currently taking about a yearto process those I.D. cards. The spokeswoman says if you need verification oflawful entry in the United States, you should visit the INS office andcomplete form G-639. Otherwise, hold onto the card with your maiden name untilyou receive the corrected card.  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911209  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  December  </MONTH><PG.COL>  5C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  423  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday, December 9, 199100344200,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>